Fetal Health Classification

A machine learning project to classify fetal health into 3 categories
based on Cardiotocography (CTG) exam data.

Classes
- 1 — Normal
- 2 — Suspect
- 3 — Pathological

Dataset
- 2126 records, 22 features
- Source: Kaggle — Fetal Health Classification

Models Used
- Logistic Regression — Baseline model
- SVM RBF Kernel — Best single model
- Random Forest — Good with feature selection
- Gradient Boosting — Strong ensemble learner
- Voting Classifier — Combined all models soft voting

What I Did
- Exploratory Data Analysis EDA
- Correlation heatmap and scatter plots
- Feature selection based on correlation
- Hyperparameter tuning with GridSearchCV
- 5-Fold Cross Validation

Tech Stack
- Python
- Pandas, NumPy
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib, Seaborn

